metadata.subject: Proposal regarding JASTA impact on KSA

relationships.description: Served as White House Counsel to President Obama
Served as Associate Counsel to President Clinton
Conducted investigation of Clinton administration including Monica Lewinsky affair
Litigation partner at Washington, D.C. office

analysis.purpose: To propose an approach to address the impact of JASTA on Saudi Arabia politically and economically
analysis.significance: Appears to be a consulting proposal leveraging high-profile legal and political figures to address Saudi Arabia's concerns about JASTA legislation

red_flags: Proposal involving former high-level government officials for foreign government interests
Mention of payment methods and success fees without details

blackmail_indicators.description: No indicators of blackmail or coercion found in this document

illegal_activity.description: No illegal activity evidence found - this appears to be a legitimate consulting proposal

public_knowledge.context: JASTA (Justice Against Sponsors of Terrorism Act) was controversial legislation allowing lawsuits against foreign governments for terrorism-related activities. The involvement of high-profile figures like Ruemmler and Starr with Saudi interests would be of media interest.

analysis.summary: This proposal outlines an approach to address the political and economic impact of JASTA on Saudi Arabia, featuring high-profile legal figures Kathryn Ruemmler (former White House Counsel) and Ken Starr (former Independent Counsel) as potential leaders for the initiative.
